            <title>[PIG-3520] Provide backward compatibility for PigRunner and PPNL after PIG-3419</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3520</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3419&quot; title=&quot;Pluggable Execution Engine &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3419&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3419&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; did backend refactory to support multiple backend. However, it break backward compatibility of two widely used API: PigRunner and PPNL. And it does not provide a deprecate path. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
